Re: ii desu ka
by Kansha » Sun 02.21.2010 11:18 am Arigato! (jotting down notes..) maybe we'll encounter the katta, kute and all other forms on our Basic 2 class. thanks a lot for sharing, i really appreciate it. All along i thought simply by making 'desu' to 'deshita' would make it past tense.. i.e oishii desu to oishii deshita, but now i see you can add the katta and make it 'oishikatta desu' (it was delicious). Yey! thank you again! i have two more questions though.. is 'oishii deshita' gramatically wrong? when is it more appropriate to use 'deshita' in a sentence? Thank you again so SO MUCH. Gambarimasho! Kansha
