Re: ii desu ka
by ピーター » Sun 02.21.2010 11:26 am I'm also not very far along in my studies, but it's my understanding that 'oishii deshita' is grammatically wrong, and would always be. It's only appropriate to use 'deshita' when you're dealing with an adjective with a long form ending in 'na', such as 'kireina'. 'i' form adjectives such as 'oishii' always use 'katta desu' format for affirmative past tense I believe.
